The paper presents two novel approaches to solving the classic board game Mastermind using search algorithms. These approaches involve simulated annealing and maximum expected reduction in consistency, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.AI). The paper also compares the results of these algorithms to two baseline search methods, which involves analyzing data and making predictions (cs.LG). The game of Mastermind involves guessing a secret code, which can be seen as a game of strategy and decision-making (cs.GT). The algorithms used in the paper involve searching through possible solutions, which can be seen as a problem in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper involves implementing and testing these algorithms, which can be seen as a software engineering problem (cs.SE).
